#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cllm-provider-architecture.md:76
msgid "Response delivery: streaming vs. buffered"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cllm-provider-architecture.md:78
msgid ""
"`onDelta` is called per token as the stream arrives. This produces a visible "
"build-up effect in the assistant bubble — the user sees progress during long "
"multi-tool queries rather than a blank wait followed by a sudden full "
"response."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cllm-provider-architecture.md:80
msgid ""
"The pre-registry behavior (one emission of the full text after "
"`stream.finalMessage()`) can be restored in `AnthropicLlmProvider.streamTurn"
"()` by buffering and emitting once:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cllm-provider-architecture.md:81
msgid ""
"// Buffered (all-at-once) variant\n"
"const response = await stream.finalMessage();\n"
"const text = response.content\n"
"  .filter((b): b is Anthropic.TextBlock => b.type === 'text')\n"
"  .map((b) => b.text)\n"
"  .join('');\n"
"if (text) onDelta(text);"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cllm-provider-architecture.md:91
msgid ""
"The streaming variant is the current default. Which is preferable is subject "
"to user feedback."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cllm-provider-architecture.md:95
msgid "Frontend — model selector"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cllm-provider-architecture.md:97
msgid "`GET /v1/mcp/models` returns all available models with their provider:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cllm-provider-architecture.md:98
msgid ""
"export interface LlmModelEntry {\n"
"  id: string;\n"
"  displayName: string;\n"
"  providerId: string;\n"
"  providerDisplayName: string;\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cllm-provider-architecture.md:107
msgid ""
"`McpChatSection` fetches this on mount and renders a `<select>` below the "
"source toggles when more than one model is available. The selected `modelId` "
"is sent on every `POST /v1/mcp/chat` request. When only one model is "
"available the selector is hidden."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cllm-provider-architecture.md:111
msgid "Adding a new provider"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cllm-provider-architecture.md:113
msgid ""
"Create `packages/backend/src/services/llm/YourLlmProvider.ts` implementing "
"`LlmProvider`. Declare `meta.models` with the model IDs you want to expose. "
"Implement `toYourMessage()` to convert `AgentMessage` to the SDK's native "
"format and handle the `assistant_tool_use` / `tool_results` roles."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cllm-provider-architecture.md:114
msgid "Add the API key to `Config` in `config.ts` and to `.env.example`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cllm-provider-architecture.md:115
msgid "Register in `packages/backend/src/index.ts`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cllm-provider-architecture.md:116
msgid "llmRegistry.register(new YourLlmProvider());"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cllm-provider-architecture.md:120
msgid ""
"The new provider's models appear in `GET /v1/mcp/models` immediately after "
"deployment, as long as `isAvailable()` returns `true`."
msgstr ""
